WMU surrounding Grande Prairie. Lots of concern over mule deer and elk populations. High priority on all special licences. Still has an antlerless moose season which has higher management risk than calf or bull-only units. Mule deer populations have been depressed for many years and there is significant local concern.

Highest ungulate damage compensation claims in province, up to 80% in some years. We haven't flown this unit for elk since 2014. Saddle Hills County has requested that our Minister meet to discuss elk management and local County newsletters are indicating a  push for a general antlerless season. We also have many special licence seasons and will be proposing a Regulation change to align the antlerless white-tailed deer season with adjacent units. This unit also has a calf moose and high priority to attain a bull mooose licence.

Long overdue, many special licence seasons including calf moose, antlerless elk, antlered and antlerless mule deer. Proposing regulation change to align antlerless white-tailed deer season with adjacent units. Agricultural conflict with elk is high.
